## 📄 1. app.js

```js
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.send("Docker Node App Running!");
});

app.listen(3000, "0.0.0.0", () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
🔍 Explanation
express() → server create karta hai
app.get("/") → route define
"0.0.0.0" → container ke bahar se access allow

👉 Agar "localhost" use kiya:

Container ke bahar access nahi milega ❌
📄 2. Dockerfile
FROM node:18-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY package.json .
RUN npm install
COPY app.js .
EXPOSE 3000
CMD ["node", "app.js"]
🔍 Line-by-Line
Line	Meaning
FROM node:18-alpine	Lightweight Node base image
WORKDIR /app	Working directory set
COPY package.json .	Dependencies file copy
RUN npm install	Install dependencies
COPY app.js .	Copy app code
EXPOSE 3000	Declare port
CMD ["node", "app.js"]	Run app
📄 3. package.json
{
  "name": "node-docker-app",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "app.js",
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "^4.18.2"
  }
}
🔍 Purpose
Dependencies manage karta hai
Docker build ke time use hota hai
⚠️ Rename Dockerfile
Rename-Item Dockerfile.txt Dockerfile
🧠 Why?

Docker sirf exact naam Dockerfile recognize karta hai
.txt extension → ignore ho jayega ❌

🚀 Build and Run
Step 1: Build Image
docker build -t node-app .

👉 Hinglish:
“Is folder se ek image bana do”

Step 2: Run Container
docker run -d -p 3000:3000 node-app
Part	Meaning
-d	Background run
-p 3000:3000	Port mapping
node-app	Image name
Step 3: Test

Open browser:

http://localhost:3000

Expected:

Docker Node App Running!
⚠️ Common Mistakes
❌ 1. localhost use karna
Container accessible nahi hoga

✅ Use:

"0.0.0.0"
❌ 2. Dockerfile.txt
Docker ignore karega
❌ 3. Wrong COPY order

Bad:

COPY . .
RUN npm install

Problem:

Har build me dependencies reinstall (slow)
✅ Correct Approach
COPY package.json .
RUN npm install
COPY app.js .

👉 Fast builds (cache use hota hai)

⚡ Build Optimization
Approach	Result
Copy all first	Slow ❌
Copy package.json first	Fast ⚡
